<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en" lang="en">
<head>
	<meta charset="UTF-8" />
	<title>Perl6Citations</title>
	<link rel="stylesheet" href="min.css" />
	<link rel="stylesheet" href="second.min.css" />
	<link href="favicon.ico".
		rel="shortcut icon"
		type="image/x-icon">
        <script type="text/javascript"
            src="dygraph-combined.js">
        <script type="text/javascript"
            src="extra/synchronizer.js">
        </script>
        <style> 
            .dygraph-legend > span { display: none; }
            .dygraph-legend > span.highlight { display: inline; }
        </style>
</head>
<body>
	<div class="container">
		<header class="panel panel-primary lead">
			<div class="panel-heading">
				<h1 class="panel-title">Ecosystem Citation Index</h1>
			</div>
			<div class="panel-body suckin-btm">
				<img class="pull-right" alt="»ö«" id="logo" src="camelia-logo.png">
				<p>A citation index is calculated for all the <TMPL_VAR N_MOD> modules in the 
				<a href="http://modules.perl6.org">Perl6 Ecosystem</a> on <TMPL_VAR DATE>.</p>
				<p>A total of <TMPL_VAR N_CIT> <i>Topline</i> Modules in the Ecosystem</a>
					 were cited, or <TMPL_VAR PC_CIT> of the Ecosystem Modules.</p>
				<p>The Citation Index is defined as <code>100 * # times cited by any module / # cited modules</code></p>
				<P>Data is gathered from Ecosystem projects file (used by panda). 
					A module <I>simply cites</I> another
					if it lists it in the <B>"depends"</B> list. A module <I>recursively cites</I> another if a cited 
					module in turn cites another module.</P>
                                <P>The simple and recursive data are graphed for the top TMPL_VAR GR_NUM modules over the last TMPL_VAR N_DATES.<P>
				<P>The citation indices of the top <TMPL_VAR N_ROWS> <i>topline</i> modules are given later.</P>
			</div>
		</header>
		<table class="table table-condensed">
                    <tr>
                        <th align="center">Simply Cited</th><th align="center">Recursively Cited</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><div class="panel panel-default" id="simple"></div></td>
                        <td><div class="panel panel-default" id="recursive"></div></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <th colspan="2" align="center">All Module Numbers</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td colspan="2"><div class="panel panel-default" id="allmods"></div></td>
                    </tr>
		</table>
		<div class="panel panel-default">
			<div class="table-responsive">
			  <table class="table table-condensed table-striped panel-body" id="dists">	
			    <thead>
			      <tr>
			        <th></th>
			        <th colspan="4" style="text-align: center">Sorted in simple order</th>
			        <th></th>
			        <th colspan="4" style="text-align: center">Sorted in recursive order</th>
			      </tr>
			      <tr>
			        <th></th>
			        <th colspan="2" style="text-align: center">Simple</th>
			        <th colspan="2" style="text-align: center">Recursive</th>
			        <th></th>
			        <th colspan="2" style="text-align: center">Simple</th>
			        <th colspan="2" style="text-align: center">Recursive</th>
			      </tr>
			      <tr>
			        <th>Module Name</th>
			        <th>Order</th>
			        <th>Index</td>
			        <th>Order</th>
			        <th>Index</td>
			        <th>Module Name</th>
			        <th>Order</th>
			        <th>Index</th>
			        <th>Order</th>
			        <th>Index</th>
			      </tr>
			    </thead>
			    <tbody>
			      <TMPL_LOOP modules>
			      <tr>
			        <td class="name"><TMPL_VAR s_name></td>
			        <td><TMPL_VAR s_s_ord></td>
			        <td><TMPL_VAR s_s_sim></td>
			        <td><TMPL_VAR s_r_ord></td>
			        <td><TMPL_VAR s_r_rec></td>
			        <td><TMPL_VAR r_name></td>
			        <td><TMPL_VAR r_s_ord></td>
			        <td><TMPL_VAR r_s_sim></td>
			        <td><TMPL_VAR r_r_ord></td>
			        <td><TMPL_VAR r_r_rec></td>
			      </tr>
			      </TMPL_LOOP>
			    </tbody>
			  </table>
			</div>
		</div>
		<TMPL_IF ErrorsExist>
		<footer class="panel panel-primary">
			<div class="panel-heading">
				<h1 class="panel-title">Errors</h1>
			</div>
			<div class="panel-body suckin-btm">
				<P>The <B>depends</B> list of a <I>topline</I> ecosystem module sometimes contains a module name that is
				not itself a topline ecosystem module, but may be in a sub-directory of another module 
				that is normally included.
				It is possible that such a reference could
				cause an installation failure if the module cannot be directly found. </p>
				<P>The <I>Test</I> module is explicitly excluded from this list.</p>
				<P>Naturally, the errors listed here may be an artifact of the algorithm. Kind suggestions always welcome at rnhainsworth at the main gmail domain.</p>
				<P>These cited non-topline modules are:</p>
				<table class="table table-condensed table-striped panel-body">
					<thead>
						<tr><th>Module Name</th><th>Cited by</th></tr>
					</thead>
					<tbody>
						<TMPL_LOOP ErrorLoop>
						<tr><td><TMPL_VAR ModName></td><td><TMPL_VAR CitedBy></td></tr>
						</TMPL_LOOP>
					</tbody>
				</table>
			</div>
		</footer>
		</TMPL_IF>
		<footer class="panel panel-primary">
                    <P>Graphs drawn with package from <A href="http://dygraphs.com/">Dynagraphs</A>. </P>
                </footer>
	</div>
	<script type="text/javascript">
	var g = new Dygraph(
            document.getElementById("recursive"),
            "GraphFile_recursive.csv",
            {   width: 480,
                height: 320,
                stackedGraph: 0,

                highlightCircleSize: 2,
                strokeWidth: 1,
                strokeBorderWidth: 1,
                
                series: { 
                    'ModulesCited': { axis: 'y2', strokeWidth: 3, drawPoints: true, pointSize: 3.5 }, 
                    'AllModules': { axis: 'y2', strokeWidth: 3, drawPoints: true, pointSize: 3.5 }
                },
                axes: { 
                    y: {valueFormatter: function(y) { return y.toFixed(2) + '%' }, axisLabelFormatter: function(y2) { return y2.toFixed(0) + '%' } },
                    y2: {valueFormatter: function(y2) { return y2.toFixed(0) }, axisLabelFormatter: function(y2) { return y2.toFixed(0) }}
                },

                highlightSeriesOpts: {
                strokeWidth: 3,
                strokeBorderWidth: 1,
                highlightCircleSize: 5
            }}
            );
        var h = new Dygraph(
            document.getElementById("simple"),
            "GraphFile_simple.csv",
            {   width: 480,
                height: 320,
                stackedGraph: 0,

                highlightCircleSize: 2,
                strokeWidth: 1,
                strokeBorderWidth: 1,
                
                series: { 
                    'ModulesCited': { axis: 'y2', strokeWidth: 3, drawPoints: true, pointSize: 2 }, 
                    'AllModules': { axis: 'y2', strokeWidth: 3, drawPoints: true, pointSize: 2 }
                },
                axes: { 
                    y: {valueFormatter: function(y) { return y.toFixed(2) + '%' }, axisLabelFormatter: function(y2) { return y2.toFixed(0) + '%' } },
                    y2: {valueFormatter: function(y2) { return y2.toFixed(0) }, axisLabelFormatter: function(y2) { return y2.toFixed(0) }}
                },

                highlightSeriesOpts: {
                strokeWidth: 3,
                strokeBorderWidth: 1,
                highlightCircleSize: 5
            }}
            );
        sync = Dygraph.synchronize( g,h, { selection: true, zoom: false } );
        </script>
</body>
</html>
